Package: psdness
Title: Certify Whether a Rounded Correlation Matrix Can be Positive Semidefinite
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ian", "Hussey", email = "ianhusseysipod@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Forensic metascience tool that decides whether a reported
    correlation matrix, whose off-diagonal entries are rounded to fixed
    precision, is consistent with any positive semidefinite (PSD) matrix
    inside the induced rounding box. The payload is certifying
    IMPOSSIBILITY: when no PSD matrix fits the rounding box, the reported
    matrix cannot be a genuine correlation matrix. Impossibility verdicts
    are backed by a rigorous a-priori floating-point error bound on a
    witness-vector quadratic form (Higham, "Accuracy and Stability of
    Numerical Algorithms", 2002), so they do not depend on solver
    tolerances. Possibility is certified by exhibiting an in-box PSD matrix
    verified via a one-sided Cholesky test (Rump, "Verification of positive
    definiteness", BIT 46:433-452, 2006).
